Bobs, basically animating a software sprite, like so:

1. read the gfx data from under where the sprite will go

2. Past gfx over the area

3. Wait until the image moves/changes, paste original data back over
and 
go to step 1.


Without double buffering, that can be quite flickery, although if you
time it nicely with the vbl update it might not be so bad.



Of course, one thing you could do is have your virtual girl confined
her own window, then it's simply a case of updating the gfx in the
window, you can even stick a nice backdrop in there.

