Subject: @{b}Re: transparent windows.@{ub}

Someone wrote:

>>>> I've got the problem to make partially transparent window. The
>>>> is to make it always on top. So the problem is: how could I
>>>> view under my window, with changing windows there? Or
>>>> other solutions?

When you open a window, all drawn to the windows below will be clipped.
So unless they are of type 'smart refresh' then there actually isn't
anything below your window that you can read.

To periodically close and reopen your window will trigger a redraw of
the windows below you, but effectively intuition just sends refresh
messages to each window-owner, so you'd have to monitor the damage
region of each window, to see when it gets cleared (which indicates
that the program has updated the damaged part). And there's no nice way
to do this...

If you're just playing around (i.e. don't care about hacks) then you
could probably patch DoHookClipRects(). This function is used by
graphics.library each time rendering takes place. What it does is it
calls the given hook for each visible rectangle associated with the
rastport. You'd want to extend it so that it also calls the hook for
the rectangles obscured by your window (providing an off-screen bitmap
to the hook).

Good luck! :-)

Regards Allan





