> I have found the problem. The problem are commands "Forbid() & Permit()".
> What is the effect from this?

They disable and enable multitasking.
In ARexx code they are usually around FindPort() und PutMsg(). This is to
avoid that the port you found with FindPort() closes (e.g. when the program
owning the port exits) before you have sent the message with PutMsg(). This
would leave you with an invalid pointer, which PutMsg() obviously doesn't
like...

So you can't remove Forbid() and Permit(), there has to be some other
problem with your code.

