Are you sure that task code is executed?? You used the same name for struct
Task pointer as the task main function... And you have no __saveds and __asm
keywords in task function definition (make sure that they're not necessery or
use them).

Couple words about your's code:

- Don't hold Forbid()/Permit() state for long time. Functions which allocate
memory (etc. CreateArgstring(), CreateRexxMsg() ) are very slow (it's because
AllocMem() is slow). In above code first create rexx message and when it's
ready to send use:

Forbid();
if( rexxport = FindPort( port ) ) PutMsg( rexxport, rexxmsg );
Permit();

- It's bad idea to kill process/tasks... Use message ports to ask child
process/task to quit and after it really quited (you must be sure! If you kill
child process/task when it's sending rexx message you could have troubles
(losing memory or random crashes etc.) ) then quit parent process.

- Use Processes than Tasks.

Try this SendRexxCommand() (someone fix me: isn't Answer the same structure as
rexxMsg?):

static ULONG SendRexxCommand( STRPTR Port, STRPTR Cmd, struct MsgPort
*ReplyPort, STRPTR Result )
{
   ULONG Error = RC_FATAL;
   struct RexxMsg *rexxMsg, *Answer;
   struct MsgPort *RexxPort;

   *Result = '\0';
   if( rexxMsg = CreateRexxMsg( ReplyPort, NULL, NULL) )
   {
      if( rexxMsg->rm_Args[ 0 ] = CreateArgstring( Cmd, strlen( Cmd ) ) )
      {
         rexxMsg->rm_Action = RXCOMM | RXFF_RESULT;
         Forbid();
         if( RexxPort = FindPort( Port ) )
            PutMsg( RexxPort, &rexxMsg->rm_Node );
         Permit();
         while( !( Answer = (struct RexxMsg *) GetMsg( ReplyPort ) ) )
            WaitPort( ReplyPort );
#if 1
         // This can't work from tasks, instead printf();
         // you can use DisplayBeep( NULL );
        // It's only for debuging.
         if( Answer != rexxMsg ) printf( "ERROR!\n" );
#endif
         if( ( Error = rexxMsg->rm_Result1 ) == RC_OK )
         {
            if( rexxMsg->rm_Result2 )
            {
               strcpy( Result, (STRPTR) rexxMsg->rm_Result2 );
               DeleteArgstring( (UBYTE *) rexxMsg->rm_Result2 );
             }
         }
         DeleteArgstring( (UBYTE *) ARG0(rexxMsg) );
      }
      DeleteRexxMsg( rexxMsg );
   }
   return( result );
}

