them; I created couple by myself ;).

For instance BOOPSI gadgetclass which need to be refreshed, Intuition will
call OM_RENDER method and your's class dispatcher will render to provided
rastport.  Then when user do something, Intuition will call OM_HANDLEINPUT
method and you can handle specified event or pass it to other gadgets on list.

With MUI you do almost exactly the same things:  write rendering function
which will be called when MUIM_REDRAW method is called and MUIM_HANDLEEVENT
(your's code will check what user do and if it plays with your's gadget do
something), MUIM_SETUP and MUIM_CLEANUP ("New style" MUI even handling
engine requires that subclass of MUIC_Area will add and remove
EventHandlerNode to MUI window; it's more efficient than older methods).

