Hello Phillip,

On 14-Jan-01, Phillip Perez wrote:
>> when i use the resize gadget to make the window smaller and
>> then resize it back the displayed text gets wiped out. 

yes; you have to repair the damaged area.

I noticed in your code at the openwindow section:

> /*--------------------------------------------------------*/
> /*          attributes                                    */
> /*--------------------------------------------------------*/
[...]
>                    WA_SmartRefresh,    TRUE,
>                    WA_SimpleRefresh,   TRUE,

You cannt specify both - your window has to be either smart or simple
refresh. The OS probably sets it to simple refresh since it was the last one
in order.
Comment out the WA_SimpleRefresh line, then the OS will handle cases where
the window is involved in depth arragement (it will repair damaged areas).
However, the OS will send your application a refresh event when it is
resized; you will have to handle this yourself. (Use WA_NoCareRefresh to
disable refresh events).

You might find the following article on the DEV-CD to be of help:
ADCD_2.1:Reference/ROM_Kernel_Manuals/Libraries_Manual (guide file).
in the "user interface libraries/Intuition Windows/preserving the window
display" section, it talks about damaged areas and refreshing.

I hope this helps.

