   I have never used GCC itself so I can not fully comment, however StormGCC
is very good.

   StormC v4 does have a v3 mode, but it is an upgrade to the public
released v3 I assume it is moe like v4 beta before they took the GCC route.

   H+P do not support v3 or v3 mode any more, they EXPECT you to be using
StormGCC!!!

   As for StormGCC it seems to be fully GCC compatible.  In both C and C++
modes.  Remember that GCC does not support registerised parameters in C++
mode so you need to do the hook/linkerlib way for MUI etc.

   The IDE is better than v3 and after a couple of my requested have been
implemented, H+P said they wouldn't be hard to do :-)  It will be even
better.

