to StormGCC without any changes apart from the MUI side where I have had to
slightly alter the way I setup my hooks to solve the register problem as I
use C++.

   As for producing code.  The final executable is slightly bigger than v3
with stormamiga.lib and the code is slightly slower than v3 and
stormamiga.lib but not by much.

   If you are a StormC user or a GCC user who would like an IDE type
environment I would recomend it!!!

