I also had problems with this in vbcc, I used SubTime() in StormC without
problems but it seams like vbcc needs some more stuff. You need to include
proto/timer.h which should have the declaration.

extern struct Library *TimerBase;

Now you also need to create that library base in your program.

struct Library *TimerBase;

Does anyone know why this is a struct Library btw, shouldn't it be a struct
Device? That works also but I get a compiler warning.

You also needs to set the library base after the device is opened before
using SubTime().

TimerBase = TimerIO->tr_node.io_Device; 
// TimerIO is your struct IORequest

Hope this helps and don't thank me for the info, thank David McMinn 'cos he
told me :)


