  You should always use const when using an object you will not change.
  An example where i use it most times is when passing arguments like:

int add( const int x, const int y ) {
    return x + y;
}

int main() {
    int number1 = 9, 
    const int number2 = 2;
    number1 = add( number1, number2 );
}

  This way you make sure add() doesnt modify its two arguments
 and you declare number2 in main as const cause its constant data!

  And there are more places/situations where const is even more important
 like in funcion overloading and so on.

