The problem I've found is that if  you  use  FD2Pragma's  special  mode  40
("create  new  style  GCC  inline files") then it causes problems with said
macros. If you use special mode 41 however ("create old  style  GCC  inline
files"),  then  it parses the macros without bother. printf() is not listed
in any inline files and so doesn't suffer from this problem.

Precisely why this is the case  will  require  further  study  of  the  two
variations of inline files, which I shall do in the future.

 
Steve




